Johannesburg- SASSA has warned its beneficiaries to update their details to avoid disappointments. “Clients who got married or change their surname at the department of home affairs are urged to update Sassa of the change. Sassa validates the client’s information with the department of home affairs monthly. If details do not match, the applications for the period may be declined,” SASSA said in a statement.  Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.